Author: DeViL303
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO/ICO]💠World Bit Bank💠The world’s first legal cryptocurrency bank💠
Body: World Bit Bank & VISA cooperation    This week is really important and full of expectations for our project. We are preparing some great news for you guys, regarding our further cooperation as well as official APP production.  While we are waiting for an upcoming news, we decided to continue an “Ask me anything” rubric and today’s question is “World Bit Bank and VISA cooperation”  Well, to begin with, we would like to say that VISA — is the world’s second-largest card payment organization. It is an American multinational financial services corporation headquartered in California, United States. It facilitates electronic funds transfers throughout the world, most commonly through Visa-branded credit cards, gift cards and debit cards.  World Bit Bank is going to become the world’s first legal cryptocurrency bank. Our project is rather widespread and unique. That is why we are going to cooperate with the world’s largest and stable financial corporations in order to provide our users with the best services.  According to the projects road-map, after ICO is finished, we are going to buy an already existing bank. After that, we will implement cryptocurrencies into its activities. Each bank, we are going to buy, has all necessary agreements with VISA, so the electronic cards we will issue would be the same as usual bank cards. The difference is: you will have an opportunity to verify your transactions in cryptocurrency. It means you can create a bank account in any fiat currency or in cryptocurrency. Surely it would be also possible to pay  https://medium.com/@coinwbb/world-bit-bank-visa-cooperation-fb0f46d9d96f

Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO/ICO]💠World Bit Bank💠The world’s first legal cryptocurrency bank💠
Body: The bank we are going to buy already has all necessary agreements with Visa. And the electronic cards we will issue would be the same as usual bank cards. The difference is: you will have an opportunity to verify your transactions in cryptocurrency. It means you can create a bank account in any fiat currency or in cryptocurrency. Surely it would be also possible to pay either in "usual" currency or in cryptocurrency where it is possible.   Now our team is developing a mobile app to make it possible for you to control your transactions online Of course other bank services are also available If a store accepts cryptocurrency the transaction will be made using blockchain technology thus faster cheaper and more secure. If not you will have to use an electronic payment system such as visa or mastercard. It would be also fast and secure but most likely more expensive Here is a short illustration https://drive.google.com/file/d/15rU4RoeAwWA_voFhsQGF0n5WOkxXAX-L/view?usp=drivesdk  Thank you very much for your genuine interest. Have a nice day!

Author: WorldBitBank
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO/ICO]💠World Bit Bank💠The world’s first legal cryptocurrency bank💠
Body: Hi Investments are really not shown on Etherscan correctly There are several reasons why: We have some obligations due to the licenses. We can't accept more than 10000 Euro without explaining where the money come from and without some necessary documents. That is why many investors prefer using our bank account directly Most of our investors now are other banks and investing funds. They do not use cryptocurrency, only Euro You may ask to show you our available balance in bank if you want to find out what is the real investments. We allowed access to this information, so you may ask Our project is quite legal and our activity is under control of banking system and government. That is why our investors understand their money is protected by law and justice, not by our promises. There are our contacts on the website or whitepaper. You may also ask government agencies for any official information about us and our activity. Please look at this project more attentively and do not judge hastily of this project. I see no real reasons to accuse our team as scammers  Thank you for your interest!

Author: Petroleumblood
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO/ICO]💠World Bit Bank💠The world’s first legal cryptocurrency bank💠
Body: Until there is no any proof of your reaching softcap, the provided information is misleading.  "We can't accept more than 10000 Euro without explaining where the money come from and without some necessary documents." So, you actually said that you have reached softcap and are not available for getting more than 10000 EUR. In this way possible few options: you lied about reaching softcap or you have violated the law by getting much more than 10k. Both options cause specific penalties according the laws of EU.  "Most of our investors now are other banks and investing funds. They do not use cryptocurrency, only Euro" I hope, they know that you are not available for getting more than 10k EUR?  "You may ask to show you our available balance in bank if you want to find out what is the real investments. We allowed access to this information, so you may ask" This info must be public. Not "by request". The names of banks and funds must be also published for avoiding violation of AML conditions.  "Our project is quite legal and our activity is under control of banking system and government. That is why our investors understand their money is protected by law and justice, not by our promises. " Still there is no any proof of existance of so-called "investors".  "You may also ask government agencies for any official information about us and our activity. Please look at this project more attentively and do not judge hastily of this project." Of course I will. I wouldn't say that if I didn't read the whitepaper.  "I see no real reasons to accuse our team as scammers  Thank you for your interest! "  Of course you don't. You are welcome.

Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO/ICO]💠World Bit Bank💠The world’s first legal cryptocurrency bank💠
Body: Can you talk more about licenses?    What are they needed for? Why do others (similar projects) not receive them? Why do you need them? What do they give?  Do you have international or local licenses?   Sorry, ate I ask stupid questions, but I really do not understand and I want answers.

Author: WorldBitBank
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO/ICO]💠World Bit Bank💠The world’s first legal cryptocurrency bank💠
Body: Hi, No, it's not a stupid question License is an official document which allows us to perform any activity legally. In our case it's cryptocurrency transactions. It's completely impossible to create WBB without these licenses - it won't be legal. Our company is registered in Estonia where we've got our licenses. They are local but valid for the whole EU and for many other countries. License is a guarantee that we are on a right way and do everything legally. For our investors it's a confidence that our project is not a flimflam and we will not disappear with their money. We are not able to answer what do other companies and why they avoid licences and transparency. We confess many projects prefer such a rule: everything what is not prohibited is obviously allowed. But it's not always so. Licenses give us trust and it is the most important thing in our business.  In the nearest future we will post a video with our expert explaining licenses and why they are important for us.  Thank you for a good question. Wish you a nice day!

Author: GoG-Alpha
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO/ICO]💠World Bit Bank💠The world’s first legal cryptocurrency bank💠
Body: Conceptually the idea is good and many have thought it.  Good to see a group making it happen.    My main concern are the timelines being unbelievably ambitious to be realistic... acquiring 10 banks in just over a year. Even if you have the money I doubt it's legally/procedurally possible to move that fast; the paperwork from lawyers alone I imagine would take longer than a year to takeover 10 banks.  That said, good luck!  True transparency in baking would be revolutionary.  As for other comments like "finally somebody making crypto legal".  Crypto is not illegal.  Crypto cannot be illegal.  Just like cash or gold asset cannot be illegal.  If your country considers crypto a currency or an asset-of-value and you do not declare it for taxable purposes chances are you are committing a crime but the crypto itself is not illegal.  Cash is not illegal, you can use it for illegal purposes but the cash itself is not illegal.  I make this point because many outside of the crypto community think crypto is illegal which is uninformed (at best), so we should try to at least have the proper perception and terminology within the crypto community itself.

Author: WorldBitBank
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO/ICO]💠World Bit Bank💠The world’s first legal cryptocurrency bank💠
Body: The licenses are issued by Estonian Police and Border Guard Board, for 1. Providing a virtual currency wallet service 2. Providing services of exchanging a virtual currency against a fiat currency What makes us stand out from our competitors is that we've obtained those licenses before even going to Pre-ICO, everything is transparent from the very beginning. Thus, we're regulated by the laws of the European Union, same as our investors are protected by the laws of European Union.
